sections.content:
(a) to  enforce,  carry  out  and  give  effect  to  the  provisions  of  the 
Dangerous  Drugs  Act  1952  except  for  sections  4,  5,  7,  paragraph 
9(1)(a), section 11 , subsection 12 (1) and sections 16 and 17;

(b) to enforce, exercise, discharge and  perform the powers, duties and 
functions under the Drug Dependants (Treatment and Rehabilitation) 
Act 1983;

(c)  to enforce, exercise, discharge and perform the powers, duties and 
functions under the Dangerous Drugs (Special Preventive Measures) 
Act 1985;

(f)  to  lend  assistance  in  any  misuse  of  dangerous  drugs  matters  on  a 
request by a foreign State as provided under the Mutual Assistance 
in Criminal Matters Act 2002 [Act 621];
